programme.desc: New insights on Nolan Cross suggest a Templar connection to the Money Pit while emerging, hard evidence convinces the team the discovery of the lead cross may be the most historic find in North America.

programme.title: The Curse Of Oak Island S6E8
programme.desc: After years of searching, the team may have located a previously discovered artifact that has been missing for more than a century. In Smith's Cove, the Laginas struggle to hold back the waters.

programme.title: The Curse Of Civil War Gold S2E6
programme.desc: Kevin Dykstra and his team learn that their search for a fortune in gold at the bottom of Lake Michigan may be connected to the assassination of President Abraham Lincoln.

programme.title: The Tesla Files S1E1
programme.desc: Researcher Marc Seifer recruits astrophysicist Travis Taylor and journalist Jason Stapleton to help unravel the mystery of inventor Nikola Tesla's missing files, confiscated by the US.

programme.title: The Pickers S12E19
programme.desc: Mike and Frank head across the USA searching for iconic items that are as American as Apple Pie and Baseball.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E10
programme.desc: Greer sees LA from a whole new angle, thanks to local guide and travel consultant Kelly. We're talking rooftop bars, a rooftop cinema, skyline dining and she even gets in the water to learn to surf at Venice Beach. It's a full 48 hours in LA and, for Greer and Kelly, this is just the tip of the iceberg...

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E13
programme.desc: In this episode we learn all about Icebergs, the many ways to hurt yourself jumping off a pier, and what to watch out for the next time you are biking over a teeter totter.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E14
programme.desc: In this engineering special we discover the secrets behind explosive demolitions, exactly how dams work, and what you need to look out for when operating a ladder.

programme.title: China's Vision Of The Future E1
programme.desc: China is on the move - re-imagining how its people travel both within the country and abroad. Using autonomous and electric car and passenger drones to solve congestion and pollution, building vast bullet trains networks to link smart mega-cities of the future, and even world-beating mega ports to dominated the world of international trade through the expansion of the Old Silk Road. How well it manages this new world of trade, over the next 30 years, has the potential to become one of the defining moments of the 21st century, not just for China, but for us all.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E7
programme.sub-title: The Search For Intelligent Life On Earth
programme.desc: A revelation of the hidden underground network that is a collaboration of four kingdoms of life, and a true first contact story between humans and beings who communicate in a symbolic language and have maintained a representative democracy for many tens of millions of years.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E8
programme.desc: The mysterious untold story of the scientist who figured out how to go the Moon while fighting for his life in a WWI trench. He wrote a letter to fifty years in the future. It made the Apollo Mission possible. And the saga of the twenty-year long odyssey of a robotic explorer ordered to commit suicide on another world.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E5
programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Manuel Noriega to rise from poverty to become dictator of Panama for six tumultuous years in the 1980s. As Chief of Intelligence he was the most feared man in Panama. He developed connections inside and outside the country that made him rich, powerful, and a key ally of the US in the region, while also working for Fidel Castro and the Medellin drug cartel, among others.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E11
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans solves one of the world's great mysteries - the identity of the Loch Ness Monster. Comparisons with the deepest lake on Earth - Lake Baikal in Russian Siberia, combined with military-grade scanning technology and a sonar curtain drawn across its entire surface - the plug is pulled on Scotland's famous loch. As the waters drain away, much more than a monster is revealed.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E9
programme.desc: On this episode, agents from the Antinarcotics Division of the Jorge Chavez Airport in Lima, Peru, must not only stop a woman trying to smuggle drugs in three different modalities, but also protect her life, as one of these modalities is extremely dangerous: she is carrying the drugs inside her vagina. In the meantime, a passenger shocks the agents by claiming he is a police informant, in an attempt to delay his judicial process. Later, officers will face the arduous task of inspecting an enormous shipment of contaminated capsules.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E1
programme.desc: Susan Haglof moves to Egypt with her husband and adopts a newborn, named Marko. However Marko doesn't come with any papers and there is no proof that Susan is his adoptive mother. Hence she makes the decision to buy a birth certificate with her and her husband's name on it. Less than a year later, Susan is charged and facing jail time, however the worst is she may never see Marko again.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E5
programme.desc: What does it take to prepare over 10,000 meals a day for discerning clients of the Indian Railways and more? IRCTC shows you how it's done inside one of its central mega kitchens.

programme.title: Japan: Between Earth And Sky E3
programme.desc: Japan is an archipelago of immeasurable natural wealth. The large southern islands, Shikoku, Kyushu and Okinawa, with their relaxed atmosphere, are the cradle of Japanese spirituality. Amid spectacular landscapes, this journey between sea and sky to discover the mystical and wild islands of the South will reveal the face of a secret Japan.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E1
programme.desc: Long-time resident of Lawless Island, Gary Muelberger has seen it all. A fisherman. A trapper. His roots to Lawless Island are deep and his knowledge of how to subsistence live unmatched.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E2
programme.desc: China is the world's longest continuous civilization, but as the nation modernizes, there's a new thirst to rediscover its roots. Historian Sam Willis investigates the importance of the family to Chinese civilization and how it became the building block of Chinese society, shaping the nation from past to present.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E5
programme.desc: After abandoning his former home due to lack of resources, hunter-gatherer Matt journeys to the lower elevation canyons of southern Utah to find a new area to call home. He's hopeful this land will have the necessary resources he needs to survive the cold months. Winter has finally come, so Matt must work quickly to build a permanent shelter and protect himself from the elements.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5 Compilations E8
programme.desc: Whether it's an equipment snag at sea, a family feud at the worst possible time, or wicked weather pummeling the fleet, there seems to be a never-ending list of obstacles getting in the way of the Outer Banks captains and their catch. This episode lets viewers follow along and guess which captains were able to overcome the odds and bag a bluefin, and which fish battles ended with a bust.

programme.title: Mega Air E8
programme.desc: Mega Air gets up close to the most bizarre air freighter on the planet, the bulbous Airbus Beluga, a flying whale that swallows entire aircraft wings. We chart the misfortunes of a wealthy, American classic car enthusiast, airfreighting one of the earliest cars ever built to a famous UK car rally; and, to much fanfare, global mega movers, UPS take delivery of a brand-new Boeing 747-8, the largest freighter made in the US.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E1
programme.desc: Car lover Chris has had his beloved, Ferrari engined, 1971 Fiat Dino coupe for nearly 25 years. The former engine mechanic had to put the restoration on hold when he was diagnosed with a rare type of cancer. Now it's up to Tim and Fuzz to get this rusting Dino back to its best. Tim takes a drive in one of the most beautiful cars in the world and Fuzz gets his hands on a Ferrari racing engine for the very first time.

programme.title: Taboo S9E1
programme.desc: People have expressed their passions through their collections throughout history, but some collectors' passions cross the line into obsession. Meet a Londoner who fills his home with tiny human skeletons and shrunken heads, a self-proclaimed “Filipino Superman” who has undergone a series of cosmetic surgeries to resemble his superhero and a Utah resident who has 550 animals living in his home.

programme.desc: As their habitat shrinks and their wild prey declines, the tigers of Chitwan National Park in Nepal attack people more frequently. Gordon travels to Nepal to look into the increasing reports of man-eating tigers and investigates one particular tigress named Nangara Pothi, meaning the claw, who has killed at least ten people since 2008, unlocking the myths and mysteries of the serial man-eater.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E6
programme.sub-title: Dave Bautista In Glen Canyon, Arizona
programme.desc: Bear Grylls takes former WWE world champion and action star Dave Bautista on a super-sized adventure in the Arizona desert. Navigating through perilous canyon descents, brutal falls and the raging Colorado River will be no easy task. With Bear as his tag team partner, Dave is up for the challenge to see if he still has that fight inside - but Mother Nature could prove to be his toughest opponent yet in this match of a lifetime!

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E9
programme.desc: Ralph and Ranen are tasked with fulfilling Afzal Kahn's dream of producing one of the fastest road cars in the world. Kahn challenges them to engineer a car to beat his Bugatti Veyron in a straight quarter mile race. Their answer is a Nissan GTR with a specialist Japanese ECU hack. In three weeks they must overhaul the GTR and take it to Santa Pod Raceway for a supercar showdown.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E7
programme.desc: Welcome to Tokyo, Greer! After meeting up with her travel guide Keiichi in the middle of the famous Shibuya intersection, Greer kicks off her 48 hours in Japan. Their adventures take them to a Ninja Restaurant, on a helicopter flight above Tokyo and so much more.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E8
programme.desc: This time, Greer delves a little deeper into a city on home turf: Darwin! Her guide is travel consultant Itimai, who has a show-stopping 48 hours lined up, including stunning Top End scenery, unique fusion cuisine and yes, catching sight of a crocodile – watch out Greer!

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E1
programme.desc: Its Bluefin Season in the Outer Banks of North Carolina, and New England's best fisherman have followed the migration down to catch a piece of the action. But, an all-time low season quota means finding Southern hospitality won't be easy. Northern and Southern fisherman fight to get the first catch and mother nature isn't taking sides.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E3
programme.desc: MIA CBP searches and questions a passenger coming from Jamaica because of his suspicious story and new suitcase. After finding anomalies in the bag, they begin to suspect he might be smuggling narcotics. JFK CBP Officers find a suspicious package containing cowboy boots and suspect something is hidden inside. At JFK, HSI opens pistons filled with cocaine, which leads to a controlled delivery and raid of the home to which the package was addressed.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E1
programme.desc: Car lover Chris has had his beloved, Ferrari engined, 1971 Fiat Dino coupe for nearly 25 years. programme.title: Brain Games S6E1
programme.desc: Actor Ted Danson and special guests The Blue Man Group play along with host Keegan-Michael Key as we learn how our brains distinguish fact from fiction. Games include identifying real vs. fake news headlines, spotting a poker face out of a group of World Series Poker Champions and figuring out which photo conveys the truth. In addition, master mentalist Lior Suchard predicts who's lying when it comes to hiding a treasured object, and Danson takes a ride through the show's mental obstacle course, known as the Gauntlet.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E9
programme.desc: Greer discovers the best Hong Kong city has to offer with the help of Alan, a local travel consultant. Their adventures include visiting the incredible Big Budda on Lantau Island, enjoying mouth-watering dim sum, early morning Tai Chi and so much more!

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E10
programme.desc: Greer sees LA from a whole new angle, thanks to local guide and travel consultant Kelly. We're talking rooftop bars, a rooftop cinema, skyline dining and she even gets in the water to learn to surf at Venice Beach. It's a full 48 hours in LA and, for Greer and Kelly, this is just the tip of the iceberg...

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E10
programme.desc: Afzal Kahn has been contacted by a client asking him to produce a vehicle capable of surviving winter conditions, taking on difficult terrain and crossing deep snow. Ralph and Ranen modify an Audi A8 to withstand -40C, fit bespoke tracks to the four corners of the vehicle and a snow plough. To make sure this vehicle stands out from the crowd even more, Afzal Kahn gives the car a complete overhaul.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E2
programme.desc: Petrol head Tony's Jaguar Mk2 has been in his family for over 40 years. Due to complications following a stomach operations he's not been able to restore the car himself and it's sat neglected in the garage for nearly two decades. With Fuzz battling to start the Jags engine and Tim having to get his hand dirty making parts it will be a race against time to get this British classic finished on time.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E3
programme.desc: The rise of modern lifestyles in China has led to the explosion of the health and fitness industry, but this is far from new. Historian Sam Willis is on a journey to explore the health practices of the ancient Chinese. From the way they understood the body and its workings, to different traditions that developed to cure disease, Sam discovers how age-old concepts still loom large in the nation today.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E2
programme.desc: JFK CBP question an elderly woman arriving from Peru. They suspect narcotics are cleverly concealed in bottles that she's carrying. At MIA, HSI carries out a daring sting, delivering cocaine that was hidden in a shipment of paintings. And at LAX, a set of unclaimed suitcases arouses suspicions. Officers believe the bags may contain contraband.

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E10
programme.desc: Afzal Kahn has been contacted by a client asking him to produce a vehicle capable of surviving winter conditions, taking on difficult terrain and crossing deep snow. Ralph and Ranen modify an Audi A8 to withstand -40C, fit bespoke tracks to the four corners of the vehicle and a snow plough. To make sure this vehicle stands out from the crowd even more, Afzal Kahn gives the car a complete overhaul.

programme.title: Is It Real? (30 Mins) E17
programme.desc: Dan Brown's controversial book, “The Da Vinci's Code,” has raised huge controversy because it had made at least a couple of damaging claims that the author insist to be fact. The documentary seeks to uncover the truth behind these claims, including claims of whether Mary Magdalene may have been the wife of Jesus, and interviews with Father William Stetson and various authors of books.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E7
programme.sub-title: Joel Mchale In Arizona Slot Canyons
programme.desc: The often clever, always snarky actor and comedian Joel McHale joins Bear Grylls in the Arizona desert for an adventure unlike any other. They set out to traverse a massive slot canyon in hopes of surviving the wild, but first they have to survive one another! Huge cliffs, nasty food, and unorthodox survival strategies abound in this hilarious misadventure!

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E3
programme.desc: Engineer Chad Zdenek joins a salvage team to tear apart the world's biggest hovercraft and reveal the engineering innovations that made it a legend of its time. In San Diego, he takes controls of the US Navy hovercraft fighting wars and saving lives around the world.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E7
programme.desc: Jordan is headed to St. Louis. Known as the gateway to the west, this city is a gateway to a wide variety of culinary delights. Jordan kicks off his journey at a restaurant close to his own heart. Guerilla Street Foods serves up Filipino cuisine with a mid-west riff. Pork served street style with calamansi sauce and a poached egg, and fried chicken that finds the perfect blend of sweet, salty and tangy.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E8
programme.desc: Jordan's journey takes a turn full south with a trip to Music City. While Nashville may be best known for its music, it's next known for its mouthwatering cuisine. Jordan starts off his journey through this southern jewel at the Butcher and Bee, where globally inspired share plates bring joy to customers at all hours of the night.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E2
programme.desc: The best fisherman on the Eastern Seaboard continue their battle for bluefin in the Outer Banks of North Carolina. Last season's champion maintains his lead over both the Northern and Southern fleets. But with captains on both sides hungry for paychecks, a rapidly evaporating fish quota and an angry ocean, can the fisherman outwit the fish?

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E10
programme.desc: Taking off during a major storm, a brand-new 737 falls from the sky over West Africa, and an international group of investigators soon descends on Cameroon. Submerged in mud and water, Kenya Airlines Flight 507 crashed into a mangrove swamp, killing everyone on board. And while investigators ultimately pinpoint one fatal mistake that triggered the tragedy, they also uncover a lethal cascade of issues that sent the passenger jet spiralling toward the ground.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E7
programme.sub-title: The Search For Intelligent Life On Earth
programme.desc: A revelation of the hidden underground network that is a collaboration of four kingdoms of life, and a true first contact story between humans and beings who communicate in a symbolic language and have maintained a representative democracy for many tens of millions of years.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E8
programme.desc: The mysterious untold story of the scientist who figured out how to go the Moon while fighting for his life in a WWI trench. He wrote a letter to fifty years in the future. It made the Apollo Mission possible. And the saga of the twenty-year long odyssey of a robotic explorer ordered to commit suicide on another world.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E2
programme.desc: Actress Tiffany Haddish and director Jordan Peele join Keegan-Michael Key to play games that show how Hollywood pros manipulate our brains to make us feel genuine emotion while watching movies. Challenges and demos include taking a closer look at some of the bizarre tactics used to create sound effects in movies, spotting the stuntman, identifying a performer in disguise and illuminating how filmmakers manipulate our brains with editing. Sound designer Craig Pennigan shows us how sound alters the way our brains perceive a scene, Haddish tests her mental strength and agility in the Gauntlet, and mentalist Lior Suchard stuns the crowd with an amazing mind-reading trick.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E9
programme.desc: Jordan's southern tour continues in the jewel of the south – Charleston, South Carolina. He starts off his trip at one of the city's finest taprooms, Craftmen Taphouse where each menu items is expertly crafted to pair with one of the many beers. Jordan tucks into crowd pleasing Mexican style street fare with a zesty scallop ceviche and roasted street corn.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E10
programme.desc: Jordan is in Atlanta where cosmopolitan glamour and southern traditions collide. In this sitting, everyone is vying for a seat at the best tables, and that's even more true late night. Jordan's kicks off his Atlanta adventure at 5 Church, a midtown haven dishing out Chef Scotley's signature southern comfort.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E4
programme.desc: The Brent Delta oil rig extracted oil and gas from beneath one of the roughest seas on the planet for over 40 years. With the oil fields running dry the rig is being taken apart at a purpose-built reinforced quay on the north east coast of Britain.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E9
programme.desc: In the counterintuitive realm of quantum mechanics, light can be two contradictory things, and somehow - no one knows how - an unseen observer can alter the nature of reality. The man who stumbled on this hole in reality and the still- unfolding technological revolution that it made possible.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E10
programme.desc: Two atoms from different parts of the universe meet on a small planet. How a deadly embrace between science and state altered the fate of the world, and a gripping cautionary tale of others who grew used to living in the shadow of grave danger until it killed them all except one.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E2
programme.desc: A cargo jet plummets to earth in the Swedish Arctic. And as investigators pore over the evidence, a terrifying picture of chaos and confusion emerges.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E7
programme.desc: Miguel dresses like a scientist to produce a quick feta cheese and uses it to cook spicy harissa & couscous. Also, Miguel challenges a butcher and sets the football field as a cooking arena where he presents his masterpiece - sirloin beef pie with mushy peas and hopes to win the meat expert. Finally, Miguel's family reunites and Miguel is going to find out his mum's secret recipe.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E8
programme.desc: Miguel visits the origin of empanada in Chile where Miguel compares his grandma's Spanish empanada pie with the local Chilean empanada. Two brilliant mince recipes go head to head but only one can win the judges' hearts. Plus, Miguel savors a delicious mushroom dish and digs for the secret of making the best apple pie.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E9
programme.desc: Miguel knees in mud searching for a crab sized like a basketball. After a perspiring pull and push struggle, a crab cook-up is on show! Also, Miguel rises to a challenge of making a veggie burger and masters green eggs and ham with salsa verde with the help of some producers in South Gippsland. And finally comes the ultimate afternoon tea - Portuguese tarts which is not as hard as it seems to be.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E4
programme.desc: Peter gets to know the real Mexico as he travels on top of a 50 year old jeepney to the ghost town of Real de Catorce in search of peyote, before heading south to the romantic town of Guanajuato to learn how to make the most ubiquitous of all Mexican food, tortillas.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E5
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in one of the largest metropolises on earth, Mexico City, discovering a city of extremes with high end dining sitting side by side with some of the cheapest and tastiest street food in the world.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E6 !
programme.desc: Contrary to popular opinion, mole is not just a chilli chocolate sauce, although mole poblano is the most well-known and this episode sees Peter Kuruvita learns the secrets to this incredibly complicated concoction.

programme.title: Don't Tell My Mother S3E9
programme.desc: Diego explores where past and present collide in the biggest city in the world, Tokyo. Japan is one of the most technologically-advanced places on the planet, and in the richest city in Asia, the line between reality and fiction seems thin. From the wild to the traditional, the classic to the outlandish, discover Tokyo like you've never seen it before.

programme.title: Korean Soul Food
programme.desc: With a sound reputation of being healthy, balanced and flavorsome, Korean food has drawn global attention and attracted people around the world to visit the bustling capital city, Seoul. In the company of actress Eun-Hye Park, we'll be revealing the taste and history of a variety of popular Korean dishes, including samgyetang and bibimbap, as well as investigating their healthy cooking principal.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E10
programme.desc: Miguel dives into the sea looking for fresh Coromandel gallops in Whitianga, New Zealand. Then he undertakes a banana revival mission that it is the first time for him to be a banana farmer, and he is bent on making banoffee pie with Dulce de Leche Cream to make his effort pay off. Also, featured recipes are Stuart Oldfield and black pudding with scallop gratin.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E11
programme.desc: Miguel chases a herd of free-ranged pigs and reveals the secrets of bull-boar sausages in Daylesford. Then, he visits an Italian family who perfects the pasta recipe for generations. Last but not least, Miguel climbs up the top of a skyscraper and collects honey to prepare a traditional dessert - baklava with bee. Also featured cuisines are bull-boar bangers and porcini braised lamb shoulder.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E12
programme.desc: Miguel travels far from the central country to the North Island of New Zealand - Rotorua to explore an eccentric cuisine. He catches an eel in the river and cooks Spanish fish stew with longfin eel. Then, Miguel visits a traditional bakery which sells Italian breads made with ancient techniques. Featured cuisines include savoury beetroot salad with crunchy croutons and pain perdu.

programme.title: Ariana's Persian Kitchen E1
programme.desc: Ariana visits a bustling bazaar in Tehran where she meets a restauranteur and food blogger and taste some typical Persian fruit and dessert. Then she goes to a restaurant in the downtown area to sample classic Persian dishes, and to top it off, a high-end sweet shop that breaks the mold of the traditional Iranian pastry shop.

programme.title: Ariana's Persian Kitchen E2
programme.desc: Ariana explores the ancient city of Yazd, the bride of the desert, and takes us to a bazaar that sells spices and herbal remedies. Later she visits the oldest and most-renowned pastry shop in the city to introduce the classic dessert that she had as a child, then has a hearty meal with her friend in a restaurant housed in an ancient hammam.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E1
programme.desc: In this episode, we uncover the history and present-day stories of the colonial black and white houses built in the early 20th century in Singapore. The first one is the oldest house of its kind on the hills of Alexandra Park while the second is a grand mansion formerly lived in by a supreme-court judge, nestled within the popular district of Orchard Road. We unveil how the British lived in Singapore a hundred years ago.

programme.title: Warrior Road Trip E1
programme.desc: Boni and Lemarti are two Kenyan warriors from the Maasai and neighbouring Samburu tribe. They have been best friends since they met during warrior training when they were teenagers. But Boni and Lemarti are no ordinary Maasai. They listen to hip-hop, ride motorcycles and speak three languages. Yet it's their roots as blood-drinking warriors that define them. On their journey Boni and Lemarti share their way of life with everyone they meet, enjoying the cultural exchange of ideas and showing us 'the way of the warrior'. Their simple, naturalistic approach to life collides with the fast paced mass-consumerist society of the West. As Boni and Lemarti struggle to get their heads around western culture, we reflect on our own choices and what we take for granted. Through the eyes of these ultimate outsiders, we see we are stranger than we think.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E2
programme.desc: Deep in Morocco's Middle Atlas Mountains, Chef Ramsay embarks on an epic adventure to unlock the secrets of the Berber cuisine.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E6
programme.desc: Dr. Larry Kawa's office doubles as an orthodontics practice and a multi-aquarium showcase featuring all kinds of rare marine life. Living Color is commissioned to replace the physical tank, and also provide a unique underwater specimen to display. Mat and Francis are stumped and have to dig deep to come up with what is known as a Mermaid's Purse.

programme.title: Get Lost In Korea
programme.desc: A photographer Greg Goodman teams up with Jesse Day, a Canadian rapper living in Seoul to discover the gems of Korea. They kick off their journey in Seoul to experience the night life. Then, they head to Shinan to dig mud for octopus and swallow it alive. After the fresh cuisine, they undergo rigorous training of Zen martial arts with the monks in Andong. It's a journey of humor and friendship!

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E3
programme.desc: In a city that is still evolving in its identity in the post-Apartheid era, Johannesburg's massive street art scene has caused it to become the cutting edge of modern art in Africa. David spends the day exploring the city with local graffiti artists, learning its history, and sampling its local cuisine. From roadside braai to hipster world markets, the food in Jo'burg proves that the city is at the epicenter of Africa's multifaceted cultural explosion.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E4
programme.desc: Known for being the home of South African heroes Nelson Mandela and Desmond Tutu, the township of Soweto was, in years past, known as a rough outskirt of Johannesburg. Through the locals and their delicious home-cooked BBQ, David discovers that there's more to Soweto than meets the eye. With a powerful art and dance culture that's full of passion and energy, this tight-knit community is growing into a formidable city of its own.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E5
programme.desc: The palaces, cathedrals and museums of St. Petersburg represent some of the finest architecture on Earth. The city was built as the shining symbol of the Russian empire's golden age. But behind the gold curtain, a dark history has left some of Russia's greatest treasures on the brink. Now a select few must safeguard these cherished relics of the past to reveal the city's splendor once again.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E9
programme.desc: In the 24 hour build special George Clarke takes on the 600 year old legend of the Ty Unnos; a piece of Welsh folklore that claims that if you can build a house with four walls, a roof and have a fire burning in your hearth in less than a day, then that house and the ground beneath it is yours.

programme.title: World's Biggest Festival: Kumbh Mela
programme.desc: Film maker Diego Bunuel immerses himself in Indian culture by attending the Kumbh Mela, the world's largest religious festival that happens every 12 years. He meets sadhus who express their extreme devotion by pulling a car with penis, standing constantly for 10 years, raising an arm for 40 years and being buried alive for days! Join Diego to experience this dazzling spectacle of spiritual fervor!

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E1
programme.desc: This episode sees Christine learning firsthand the very challenging ‘how to' of harvesting sea salt in Thailand's dramatically beautiful salt fields. Cushing visits the area's most unusual market that is regularly disrupted by the Maeklong Railway going right through it's center!

programme.title: Food Lab S2E61
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys stop at Honey Tasmania on the main street of Exeter. Rebecca informs Ben about the importance of bee's and the Tasmanian rainforests. At the University of Queensland Ben cooks a chocolate espresso cake with blueberries in The Great Court. Melissa Fitzgerald explains what happens to proteins when they begin to denature.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E62
programme.desc: The last stop of the Farm Gate is York Town Organics, a family run certified organic vegetable farm. Ben has a chat with Ben Jackson, son of Claire and Bruce Jackson who pioneered the farm almost 3 decades ago. Ben and Joel are then cooking an upside down pineapple cake. In the studio, Ben uses one of his favourite fresh ingredients, wasabi, to make a salmon sashimi with avocado and wasabi puree.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E17
programme.desc: Mokukchung is the cultural capital for the Ao Nagas. Aos is one of the major Naga tribes of Nagaland. As Pablo visits Mokokchung, he gets to witness the diversity of Nagas at the Moatsumung Festival. A colorful, spirited festival that brings together the entire Naga Community.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E16
programme.desc: A 700-year-old village of the Angami Nagas is a perfect example of a close-knit community. Pablo gets a glimpse of their community culture visiting a community house followed by a community kitchen where he devours on some exotic Naga food. What surprised Pablo the most about this tribe was their transformation from fierce headhunters to farmers.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E1
programme.desc: High in Peru's Sacred Valley of the Incas, Chef Ramsay is a man on a mission, travelling by motorbike to unlock the secrets of high altitude cuisine.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E6
programme.desc: The city of Venice attracts millions of tourists each year with its rich historic and artistic heritage. Behind the vibrant facade lies a city in grave danger as the Adriatic Sea that brought glory to the city is also a threat to Venice and its lagoon. Expert teams of engineers, scientists and conservators are determined to save this World Heritage site from vanishing beneath the waves.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E1
programme.desc: Let's meet Mary who is ploughing her life savings and redundancy money into a rundown Yorkshire back to back cottage in the hope of making an impressive 25-thousand-pound profit. Working alongside a head builder who must sometimes wish she wasn't there, it's a battle against the odds from start to finish.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E1
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford joins Joe and Laura on ‘Big Blue' a 44ft Sailing Catamaran. Along the way he will jet boat up a river to a remote village, dive with huge bull sharks and track down local chef Lance Seeto to unlock an ancient local recipe.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E2
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford shows off his hometown of Gisborne. This includes hand feeding friendly wild stingrays and venturing out to his favourite fishing and diving spots trying to track down an unusual fish called a Pink Maomao. Along the way they encounter huge schools of Kingfish and a couple of friendly sharks.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E2
programme.desc: Chinese cuisines use sugar very differently from Western cuisines, and Christine starts her comparison in Paris and Athens where she looks at how Westerners interpret ‘sweet'. Traditionally, for the Chinese, sugar is predominantly used to achieve balance, but the liberal use of sugars in South East Asia Chinese cuisines are a culinary surprise.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E1
programme.desc: George travels to Suffolk to meet Simon who wants to thank his mum Carole by converting a railway cattle carriage into a luxury mobile holiday home fit for a queen. George also meets Claire in East London who, having bought her dream vintage Morris Minor Caravanette discovers it's actually rotten to the core.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E18
programme.desc: Fermentation, Alcohol & beverages: Human migration led to the spread of amazing practices in many parts of the world. People migrated with the treasure of these practices and shared them with other races. Pablo learned more about this diverse country India as he dug through the practices in North East brought by people from countries like Tibet, Burma, Laos, Vietnam.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E17
programme.desc: Mokukchung is the cultural capital for the Ao Nagas. Aos is one of the major Naga tribes of Nagaland. As Pablo visits Mokokchung, he gets to witness the diversity of Nagas at the Moatsumung Festival. A colorful, spirited festival that brings together the entire Naga Community.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E2
programme.desc: Deep in Morocco's Middle Atlas Mountains, Chef Ramsay embarks on an epic adventure to unlock the secrets of the Berber cuisine.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E6
programme.desc: The city of Venice attracts millions of tourists each year with its rich historic and artistic heritage. Behind the vibrant facade lies a city in grave danger as the Adriatic Sea that brought glory to the city is also a threat to Venice and its lagoon. Expert teams of engineers, scientists and conservators are determined to save this World Heritage site from vanishing beneath the waves.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E1
programme.desc: Let's meet Mary who is ploughing her life savings and redundancy money into a rundown Yorkshire back to back cottage in the hope of making an impressive 25-thousand-pound profit. Working alongside a head builder who must sometimes wish she wasn't there, it's a battle against the odds from start to finish.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E1
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets a small community of the Dong tribe, one of China's 55 ethnic minority groups and participates in their unusual celebration of the mid-autumn festival, a ritual marking the last harvest of the year.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E2
programme.desc: At his first stop after London, Manu arrives in Dubai where he has lined up some work in exchange for accommodations. Manu is keen on the culinary experience in Dubai so he sets off to the spice souk, fish markets, and a local pastry kitchen before having an experience of a lifetime in the desert, with food never far from the scene. Then it's onto India and a challenging train journey.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E3
programme.desc: Miami is not jut close to Cuba in proximity but the real Cuban food here is plentiful. We meet the Cubans who know the real Cuba and find out how their life here in Miami is so sweet.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E3
programme.desc: Peter gains a greater understanding of bush foods as he forages with the region's traditional owners.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E4
programme.desc: Peter uncovers a community of farmers that are focussing on sustainability before using these amazing ingredients to cook up a storm in his coastal kitchen.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E63
programme.desc: Ben heads to the Mersey Bluff, his local beach on the North West of Tasmania and cooks a vegetarian bruschetta. At The University of Queensland, Ben and Joel are going to create a tuna dish. In the studio, Ben creates a Mexican styles lasagna.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E64
programme.desc: Ben creates a chicken and pineapple tostada in the gardens at his home. At The University of Queensland Ben uses a pressure cooker to create a Mexican soup, with the help of Andrew Stevenson to explain why a pressure cooker speeds up the cook time of a recipe. In the studio Ben prepares a dish using some 16 hour slow roasted brisket, with a creamy cauliflower and wasabi puree.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E2
programme.desc: Tonight Heathrow entertain Drones, Drugs and Drunks. Meanwhile Border Force Bob is back, doing what he does best: protecting Britain's biggest border.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E1
programme.desc: Heathrow: Britain's Busiest Airport is busier than ever with drama from the get-go. Inside the terminal seasoned pro Demi dishes out deals for delayed passengers, and outside on the airfield, airside Ian is on the runway as it goes into lockdown, with a full-on armed police emergency.

programme.desc: This is a week of all things Argentinian. The dance troupe performs an Argentinian tango spectacle on the last night of the cruise and the chefs plan the gala feast with a themed menu. For the performers, the challenges are not only the dangerous acts involved in the show but also the drama during the rehearsal and the rough sea.

programme.title: Island Hunter E1
programme.desc: The Island Hunter season starts off in the beautiful and highly popular tourism hotspot; Bali. The host, Liesel Hlista embarks on a mission to understand how the Balinese blend hospitality with luxury. And this is a journey that takes place on land, underwater and even in the air! A soothing journey that finds ultra luxurious healing centers such as Como Shambhala amidst the lush jungles of Ubud - to a hands on cooking stint at the Balinese fusion restaurant Mozaic, to checking out true African style Safaris in the heart of Bali. Helicopter rides over volcanos and reef-rescuing innovative dive resorts. This is an adventure true to the Island Hunter style.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E2
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, continues his exploration of the Dong tribe and visits a village considered the living fossil of ancient traditions where he learns folk crafts from the elderly and witnesses an elaborate Dong style funeral.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E3
programme.desc: Manu takes a short flight to Mumbai and for the first time in his life, he is in India. A feast for the senses, he wants to discover as much food as he can handle. He is referred to a local Idli maker in Dharavi, who agrees to teach him the craft of Idli-making. But language isn't the only barrier for Manu as he discovers the craziness of Dharavi and its people.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E4
programme.desc: It is estimated that as many as 4.5 million Irish arrived in America between 1820 and 1930. In the 1840s, they comprised nearly half of all immigrants to this nation. They left their mark on the founding formation of America and we find out more about their history as we eat their food.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E5
programme.desc: Peter indulges his passion for seafood by diving for abalone, cooking up some local crayfish and curing trout with a delicious Margaret River gin.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E6
programme.desc: Peter completes his tour of Margaret River hosting a spectacular Beachside BBQ as part of the Gourmet Escape.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E1
programme.desc: Today's Asian adventure takes John Torode to Mumbai on the west coast of India. He begins his culinary exploration with a dusky guided tour of the street food served on Chowpatty Beach. Inspired by his cooking lessons and laden with produce from a visit to a local market, John undertakes a brand new dish of his own, Mango Samosas with a yogurt and mint dip. But are they any good?

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E1
programme.desc: Simon dreams of waking up to a peaceful view, looking out over a still lake in perfect silence. A place to escape the constant hustle and noise of life as a busy developer where he and his kids are the only ones on their very own private lake.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E3
programme.desc: Harry must assist with a medical emergency on a landing flight whilst Border Force Bob questions a circus performer from Panama. Demi saves the day again with a passenger who loses his passport.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E2
programme.desc: Tonight Heathrow entertain Drones, Drugs and Drunks. The airport runs at 98% capacity so how will the King and Queen of Terminal 2 Sue and Demi cope with the extra load from closed Gatwick? Meanwhile Border Force Bob is back, doing what he does best: protecting Britain's biggest border.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E6
programme.desc: This is the final cruise for Captain Russo and he must have the Costa Serena in perfect running order before the handover to a new captain. There is also a new itinerary and a week of intensive safety tests keeping the crew busy before he disembarks. With a new route comes a change in the entertainment schedule as well. Preparations are in full swing for the final voyage of the season.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E8
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley participates in a race pitting human runners against reindeer, five muskox undergo pregnancy tests, and Daisy participates in a family reunion.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E3
programme.desc: Step inside the most frigid habitat known to Earth - the poles. Here, the planet's ultimate survivalists include whale-hunting polar bears, leopard-seal dodging penguins and a pack of Arctic wolves that bring down a pair of musk oxen. Polar species have evolved bodies and behaviours that help them combat the intense hostility of their habitats. But now, their world is changing so fast - literally breaking apart under their feet - and their resilience will be tested beyond the extreme.

programme.title: Tree Climbing Lions
programme.desc: Big cat biologist Alexander Braczkowski is on a mission. He's got 90 days to count lions in Uganda and learn how the population is doing. But these aren't ordinary lions. The prides in Queen Elizabeth National Park spend most of their lives up in the trees, a rare and mysterious behavior unique to this part of Africa. On his journey, he'll witness mothers battling the odds to raise cubs through their first year of life, and the threats tree climbing lions face as the human population expands. Alex's experience will become more personal than he could have imagined, and he'll learn that saving lions can be about much more than counting cats.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E4
programme.desc: Mmamotse's rule has turned the Kingdom upside down. Her army run rampant, but her legacy now depends on a Princess stepping up to the throne. As the flood waters retreat, Dikeledi readies her cubs for escape, but must risk crossing enemy territory. And a run in with the Matahta Pride brings things into focus for Pula, as she begins training her young assassin. In the Savage Kingdom, the young hold the key to power - the future is theirs for the taking.

programme.title: Monster Fish S3E12
programme.desc: Dr. Zeb Hogan travels to the wild and remote Kamchatka in Russia's Far East, home to a mass migration of millions of Salmon. This isolation has preserved one of the world's last wild salmon sanctuaries, and to explore this area, he seeks help from a team of world-class kayakers and tackles white water rapids, bears, volcanoes and poachers to find out why this land is home to so many Salmon.

programme.title: Monster Fish S3E5
programme.desc: Dr. Zeb Hogan returns to the Australian Outback and comes between five giant predators battling to survive the harsh climate of the Northern Territory. For five months of the year, Giant Stingray, Sawfish, Bull Sharks and freshwater and saltwater Crocodiles become trapped in dry season waterholes, where limited food supplies mean all-out war to determine who comes out on top.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S3E6
programme.desc: Snake catcher Simon Keys and Siouxsie Gillett's business poses life and death situations. Every capture of pythons has its dangers, from an almost fatal mamba attack to the risks of being buried under a collapsing house with a snake. They conquer their fear and cope with one the world's deadliest creatures.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E1
programme.desc: A shambling hoard of zombies has invaded the airwaves, but they're nothing new. The animal world has been out-doing zombies since the beginning of time. In this episode, we go in search of nature's finest examples of zombie-like behavior.

programme.title: Wild Untamed Brazil E1
programme.desc: The forest once stretched thousands of kilometres along the Brazilian coast, but even the remaining 7% is home to many remarkable animals and unique species like muriquis, bush dogs and blue manakins. Coatimundis are one of the comical-looking ones with long noses and banded tails. But appearances can be deceptive – coatis are extremely efficient hunters.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E5
programme.desc: A good friend keeps you company when you're in need. In this episode, we feature stories of a Hawaiian surfer who hangs ten with his pet pig, a blind woman who has a guide horse, and an immobilized cat that's protected by a dachshund.

programme.title: The Pack E2
programme.desc: A single African Hunting Dog is a tough, agile predator. A pack of them is a singular force of nature, able to take on prey many times their size and strength. Travel to Umfolozi Game Reserve in South Africa, and uncover how allegiances are built, strategies planned and teamwork developed, turning these canines into an elite hunting unit.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E2
programme.desc: Borneo is the worlds third largest island, and Sumatra is no dwarf in comparison. Both islands became cut off from the Asian mainland when sea levels rose at the end of the last ice age 12,000 years ago. Large animals became marooned, isolated from their mainland cousins. Over time, they have adapted and evolved to their new home developing an array of unique traits on each island. Today, these are the Islands of Monsters.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn Compilations E1
programme.desc: Around the world, nighttime is a time of terror. In Indonesia, a bat struggles to climb past a vanguard of vipers to reach the safety of her colony. In Southern India, a mother bandicoot rat must outswim a cobra and crocodiles to find food for her babies. And in the rainforests of Costa Rica, darkness means a deadly free-for-all. Who will survive the horrors of night long enough to see the day, and who will be dead by dawn?

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E1
programme.desc: There's a baby boom in Alaska! The rescue team from the Alaska SeaLife Center hits the road when a newborn sea otter gets separated from its mom. If this baby is alright, she'll require round-the-clock care. A new baby also arrives at the Alaska Raptor Center when a bald eaglet falls from its nest. But there's no time to rest. The team must also jump into action to save a stranded, injured eagle that's lost a fight. And at the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center, two foxes rescued as kits are getting a habitat upgrade. But first they have to learn all the necessary tricks to make the big move.

programme.title: Monster Fish S3E2
programme.desc: Dr. Zeb Hogan travels to Khone Falls in Laos, one of the world's largest waterfalls, in search of the fish superhighway. Zeb hopes to see which channels fish use to migrate upriver to their spawning grounds as dams are scheduled to be built along this river, which could affect the migrations. He is joined by Trip Jennings, a National Geographic Young Explorer, and a team of world-class kayakers.

programme.title: World's Deadliest (2019) E1
programme.desc: Carnivores are designed to kill so what happens when the deadliest go head to head? Meerkats fight in the deserts, a cuttlefish turns a reef into a warzone, a killer shrew wreaks havoc in the fields, baby alligators fight to survive the deadly swamp, Lions take on hyenas and tigers take on each other as carnivores battle each other to survive Nature's eternal war.

programme.title: Man Vs Shark
programme.desc: Marine biologist and shark suit inventor, Jeremiah Sullivan, attempts to intentionally get bitten by a deadly tiger shark and survive.

programme.title: World's Deadliest Compilations E1
programme.desc: In the animal kingdom, the law is always eat or be eaten. But some sophisticated predators take down prey in brutal and terrifying ways. These are some of nature's worst ways to die, and they are neither quick nor painless.

programme.title: The World's Most Famous Tiger
programme.desc: Known as the Queen of Ranthambore, Machli is the most famous tiger in the world. The legendary tigress is a fearsome warrior known for her daring exploits. And she's the mother of an incredible four litters of cubs. She's survived longer than most tigers in the wild. Threatened by her own offspring, the aging Machli is now in jeopardy of losing her reign of the best territory inside India's Ranthambore National Park.

programme.title: 700 Sharks
programme.desc: In Polynesia, the largest school of sharks will be studied at an unprecedented scale. An international team of scientists will dive among the pack of 700 squalls. 3 years of preparation were needed to approach the sharks at night, when they are most aggressive. Using revolutionary technology and underwater filming equipment, we will reveal hunting strategies and social behaviors that will change our understanding of the world's greatest predator.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E6
programme.desc: Animals come in all shapes and sizes, born with the DNA of a survivor. If you're not the predator, you're the prey. From lion cubs to Tasmanian devils, their aggression and survival instincts are prevalent upon birth, coming out of the womb swinging. They learn the stealth, speed, and power techniques to kill as they mature. But don't underestimate the young as these animals are Born To Kill.

programme.title: Wild Cats Of India E1
programme.desc: India's big cats remain the soul of the Indian terrain - acting as charismatic ambassadors for the protection of their ecosystems. In Episode 1, watch the snow leopard guard his kill from an unrelenting red fox and follow the lives of the last surviving Asiatic lions of Gir. Using the latest camera technology, the lives of these Big Cats have been brought to our very homes in Episode 1!

programme.title: Freaks & Creeps E3
programme.desc: Lucy is in South Africa to see the enigmatic Freaky Five: cape vultures, sungazer girdled lizards, golden-brown baboon tarantulas, ground pangolins, and chacma baboons. These animals are all important to South Africans and their traditions but they have been overlooked for years. Now Lucy is on a mission to reveal the mysterious lives of those lesser-known creatures.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E1
programme.desc: Summer is in full swing in central Michigan and Pol Vet Services has revved up to meet the growing needs of their clients - from farm calls to clinic emergencies, Dr. Pol and crew are full speed ahead. But animals are not the only ones in need of Dr. Pol's attention, as he and Charles embark on a mission to fix up his vintage DMC DeLorean for the local car show.
